DITE-M1: Clinical Macro & Micro Planner 🩺
DITE-M1 is an open-source, client-side clinical decision support tool designed to automate nutritional calculations based on the ICMR-NIN (2020) Recommended Dietary Allowances (RDA) for Indians.
Developed specifically for high-volume Outpatient Departments (OPDs), Community Health Centres (CHCs), and nutritionists, this tool translates complex demographic and physiological data into instant, localized dietary targets.
🌐 Live Application: Access DITE-M1 Here (https://moulvigufran.github.io/DITE-M1)
🎯 The Clinical Problem
While the ICMR 2020 guidelines provide highly accurate, localized nutritional data tailored to the Indian phenotype, manually calculating these parameters for individual patients is time-consuming. Factoring in distinct Physical Activity Levels (PAL), precise pregnancy/lactation trimesters, and varying BMI statuses takes minutes per patient—time that is often unavailable in busy clinical settings.
💡 The Solution
DITE-M1 automates these calculations instantly. By inputting basic patient demographics, clinicians can generate a hyper-personalized, printable dietary advice report in under 30 seconds.
Key Features
  Precision BMR & TDEE: Calculates energy requirements using ICMR reference data adjusted for PAL (Sedentary, Moderate, Heavy).
  Physiological Stratification: Automatically adjusts macro and micronutrient requirements for Pregnancy (trimester-specific) and Lactation (month-specific).
  Micronutrient Tracking: Highlights critical public health markers including Iron, Calcium, Folate, and Sodium based on the latest AI/RDA guidelines.
  Zero-Data Retention: Fully client-side processing. No patient data is ever transmitted or stored on any server, ensuring strict compliance with patient privacy norms.
  Offline Capability (PWA): Installable as a Progressive Web App, allowing seamless operation in rural clinics without internet connectivity.
  Printable Reports: One-click PDF generation customized with the clinician's institutional branding.
💻 Tech Stack
  Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
  Architecture: Progressive Web App (PWA) with Service Worker caching
  Hosting: GitHub Pages
  Dependencies: None. Built entirely zero-dependency for maximum speed and security.
🚀 How to Use (For Clinicians)
1. Navigate to the Live Application (https://moulvigufran.github.io/DITE-M1).
2. Input patient demographics (Age, Gender, Weight, Height, Activity Level, and Pregnancy/Lactation status).
3. Select the clinical goal (e.g., Maintain Weight, Mild Cut for obesity management).
4. Review the generated Macro (Protein/Carb/Fat) and Micro (Vitamins/Minerals) targets.
5. Click "Generate Health Report" to print a customized diet chart for the patient.
